  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle, then rinse your <strong>quinoa </strong>in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Add the quinoa to a large pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 6-8 min or until all the quinoa is tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680277588185-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680277588185-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680277588185-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680277588185-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680277588185-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the quinoa is cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel and cut your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>red onion wedges</strong> and <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> </strong>your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 18-20 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680277592734-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680277592734-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680277592734-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680277592734-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680277592734-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680277596543-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680277596543-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680277596543-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680277596543-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680277596543-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>chickpeas</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, 50ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon[s]</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>tahini</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and your<strong> harissa paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and blitz for 1-2 min or until fully combined and smooth – this is your <strong>harissa hummus</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1680277600081-x200.jpg",
